                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 534/110.</note>
                <head>(<hi rend="italic">Handed to Acting Secretary Adee September 20, 1909, by Mr.
                        de Freyre, chargé d’affaires of Peru.</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The conflict with Bolivia has been favorably settled. Two protocols have been
                    signed. In the first protocol the Argentine award is formally accepted. And in
                    the second protocol, dated later, both parties specify certain territorial
                    compensations agreed upon within the boundary line traced by the arbitrator.</p>
            </div>
